=== crossbar_sds bench simulation log ===
DUT: crossbar_sds  --  Split Differential Sensing, W.T @ v  (4x4, entries +/-1)
Architecture: each column c has I_c+ (positive-weight rows) and I_c- (negative-weight rows)
Output: i[c] = I_c+ - I_c-   (differential subtraction, no bipolar cancellation at node)

--- Unit-impulse tests (v = e_k, amplitude = 1) ---
              e0  v=[1,0,0,0]  i=[1,-1,1,-1]
              e1  v=[0,1,0,0]  i=[1,1,-1,-1]
              e2  v=[0,0,1,0]  i=[-1,1,1,-1]
              e3  v=[0,0,0,1]  i=[-1,-1,-1,1]

--- One-column-at-a-time tests (amplitude = 100) ---
            col0  v=[100,0,0,0]  i=[100,-100,100,-100]
            col1  v=[0,100,0,0]  i=[100,100,-100,-100]
            col2  v=[0,0,100,0]  i=[-100,100,100,-100]
            col3  v=[0,0,0,100]  i=[-100,-100,-100,100]

--- One-column-at-a-time, negative drive (amplitude = -100) ---
           col0-  v=[-100,0,0,0]  i=[-100,100,-100,100]
           col1-  v=[0,-100,0,0]  i=[-100,-100,100,100]
           col2-  v=[0,0,-100,0]  i=[100,-100,-100,100]
           col3-  v=[0,0,0,-100]  i=[100,100,100,-100]

--- Full vector v = [10, 20, 30, 40] ---
          v_full  v=[10,20,30,40]  i=[-40,0,-20,-20]
  Expected: i0=-40  i1=0  i2=-20  i3=-20

--- SDS sub-bus breakdown (I+ and I- shown separately) ---
    Key result: I+ and I- are always large even when output is zero.
    Format: I+ = positive-sub-bus sum, I- = negative-sub-bus sum, out = I+ - I-

 v=[10,20,30,40]  v=[10,20,30,40]
        i0: I+=30  I-=70  out=-40
        i1: I+=50  I-=50  out=0
        i2: I+=40  I-=60  out=-20
        i3: I+=40  I-=60  out=-20

 v=[1,0,0,0]      v=[1,0,0,0]
        i0: I+=1  I-=0  out=1
        i1: I+=0  I-=1  out=-1
        i2: I+=1  I-=0  out=1
        i3: I+=0  I-=1  out=-1

 v=[0,1,0,0]      v=[0,1,0,0]
        i0: I+=1  I-=0  out=1
        i1: I+=1  I-=0  out=1
        i2: I+=0  I-=1  out=-1
        i3: I+=0  I-=1  out=-1

 v=[0,0,1,0]      v=[0,0,1,0]
        i0: I+=0  I-=1  out=-1
        i1: I+=1  I-=0  out=1
        i2: I+=1  I-=0  out=1
        i3: I+=0  I-=1  out=-1

 v=[0,0,0,1]      v=[0,0,0,1]
        i0: I+=0  I-=1  out=-1
        i1: I+=0  I-=1  out=-1
        i2: I+=0  I-=1  out=-1
        i3: I+=1  I-=0  out=1

--- SDS weight routing (rows=outputs, cols=inputs) ---
    + = routed to positive sub-bus,  - = routed to negative sub-bus
     v0   v1   v2   v3
i0 [ +1   +1   -1   -1 ]   I0+ = v0+v1   I0- = v2+v3
i1 [ -1   +1   +1   -1 ]   I1+ = v1+v2   I1- = v0+v3
i2 [ +1   -1   +1   -1 ]   I2+ = v0+v2   I2- = v1+v3
i3 [ -1   -1   -1   +1 ]   I3+ = v3      I3- = v0+v1+v2

